author: desruisseaux
msg: Metadata: FormattableObject.toString() do not convert Unicode characters to ASCII, since 'toString()' method is often used for debugging.
If the user wants a more ISO 19162 conformant string (including replacement of some non-ASCII characters), (s)he should invoke FormattableObject.toWKT() instead.
